projects.description: This project is a real-time chat application built with the MERN stack, Socket.IO, and Firebase. It enables instant communication across devices, leveraging MongoDB, Express.js, React, and Node.js for scalability. Socket.IO ensures real-time updates, while Firebase handles user authentication, database storage, and hosting, ensuring a secure and seamless user experience.

projects.name: Clone of Spotify
projects.description: This Spotify website is a comprehensive platform for song listenting, leveraging a full-stack approach. The front-end utilizes HTML, CSS, and Bootstrap to create a responsive and visually appealing user interface, with JavaScript adding interactivity. On the back-end, Node.js and Express handle server-side logic, providing a robust and scalable environment. MongoDB serves as the database, managing song listings, user information, and song details. This combination ensures a seamless and efficient experience for users seeking premium song and for song owners managing their listings.
